The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps in Borno State has arrested a 38-year-old woman, Hauwa Adamu, who allegedly drops flaming charcoal in the private parts of her seven-year-old stepdaughter. The NSCDC Commandant, Mr Abdullahi Ibrahim, told a correspondent of the News Agency of Nigeria on Wednesday in Maiduguri that the woman was arrested in the Moduganari area of Maiduguri. He said that the case was reported to the command by good Samaritans. Ibrahim revealed that Adamu allegedly meted out horrible acts of punishment on the minor, over what she called disobedience. According to him, preliminary investigations indicated that the suspect subjected the girl to different forms of abuse. Ibrahim said that the girl was put under the suspectâ€™s care sequel to the separation of her parents. He added that the case had been transferred to the National Agency for the Prohibition of Trafficking in Persons, for further investigation and action. (NAN)